    dayNumber: 19,
    whyThis: "Day 16 introduced the structural perspective — the big-picture forces that played a role in your job loss. Today goes deeper, specifically into the intersection of AI, market shifts, and personal performance. The tech industry is in the middle of a structural transformation. Companies are cutting headcount while increasing AI investment. Entire roles are being redesigned or eliminated. When you're inside that wave, it's easy to take all of it personally — to hear 'your role was eliminated' and translate it to 'you weren't good enough.' This exercise sorts specific aspects of your experience into three categories: clearly systemic (shared by thousands of people across the industry), clearly personal (genuinely about your individual choices or performance), and mixed (where structural and personal factors are tangled together). The 'mixed' category is the most important — it's where honest, nuanced self-assessment lives, away from both self-blame and self-excuse.",
    instruction: "Sort each card into one of three buckets: 'Systemic' for factors that are industry-wide or organizational (things happening to many people, not just you), 'Personal' for factors that are genuinely about your individual performance or choices, or 'Mixed' for situations where both structural and personal factors played a role. Use 'Add a card' to add your own experiences that aren't listed. When you're done, pay special attention to the 'Mixed' bucket — that's where the most honest and useful self-assessment lives. Pick one card from the 'Mixed' bucket and write a single sentence that holds both factors honestly — what was structural AND what was yours.",
