    dayNumber: 21,
    whyThis: "Day 21 closes Week 3 — the BUILD week. You've pressure-tested your values, separated structural from personal, collected evidence of competence, written your story, and refined your narrative. Now: your skills. After a job loss, it's common for confidence about your capabilities to collapse into a single feeling: 'I'm not good enough.' But skills don't work that way. You're probably strong in some areas, rusty in others, and anxious about a few where the industry has moved. The difference between a real skill gap and a fear-driven one matters — one needs a plan, the other needs perspective. This audit maps eight skill areas so you can see the full picture instead of the flattened version your anxiety produces. The shape of the wheel shows where you're actually strong, where you might want to invest, and where fear may be doing the talking rather than evidence.",
    instruction: "Drag each point on the wheel to rate your current confidence in that skill area — 1 at the center (very low confidence) to 10 at the edge (very high). Be honest, not modest. After rating all eight, look at the shape: where are you genuinely strong? Where has a skill atrophied from disuse? And where is the low rating based on evidence versus anxiety? For any rating below 4, ask yourself: is this based on something specific, or is it ambient worry? That distinction changes what you do next. For one skill area you rated below 4, determine whether the gap is evidence-based or anxiety-based. If evidence-based, identify one action to begin closing it this week. If anxiety-based, write down the counter-evidence.",
