    id: "parachute-day-23",
    name: "Three-Week Integration Review",
    modality: "integrative",
    originator: "Mindcraft / All Minds on Deck",
    primitive: "progressRiver",
    tags: ["core-parachute"],
    dayNumber: 23,
    whyThis: "You're three weeks in. Before moving into the final stretch, it's worth pausing to see how far you've actually come — because gradual change is notoriously hard to notice from the inside. Day by day, the shifts can feel small. But when you line them up — from the seven disruptions inventory on Day 1, through the identity and belief work of Week 2, through the values, evidence, and narrative building of Week 3 — the trajectory often tells a different story than the one running in your head. This isn't a progress report or a self-evaluation. It's a map. The progress river lets you plot the key moments, shifts, and surprises across the whole journey so far. You might notice that some breakthroughs came from unexpected places, or that a stuck point earlier in the program resolved itself without you realizing it.",
    instruction: "Plot key moments from your journey along the river — events, exercises, realizations, or shifts that stand out from the past three weeks. For each one, note what happened and how it felt. Some examples are pre-filled to get you started — edit or delete them and add your own. When the river is complete, look at the overall flow: where did things open up? Where did they narrow? What surprised you? This map becomes context for the final week's work. Identify one moment on the river where something opened up that you haven't acted on yet. Write down the smallest next step you could take on it this week.",
