    tags: ["core-parachute"],
    dayNumber: 24,
    whyThis: "On Day 1, you rated seven areas of disruption — income, identity, routine, confidence, belonging, purpose, and safety. That was your baseline, taken when everything was still raw. Now, 23 days later, you rate them again. This is a callback to your very first exercise, and the comparison may surprise you. Some areas will have shifted significantly. Others may be stubbornly unchanged. Both are useful information. The areas that moved show where the work landed. The areas that didn't may point to what still needs attention — or what simply needs more time. In the sandbox, the Day 1 ratings shown here are representative placeholders. In the live program, your actual Day 1 responses would be pulled in automatically.",
    instruction: "The left column shows your Day 1 ratings for each of the seven disruptions. In the right column, rate each one again on the same 1-10 scale based on where you are today. Then look at the comparison: where did you move the most? Where are you stuck? For any area that barely moved, ask yourself: is this because it genuinely hasn't shifted, or because you haven't looked at it directly? The areas that persist may need focused attention in your final week. For the area that moved the least, write one specific action you will take in the final week to address it — a conversation, a plan, a daily practice.",
