    whyThis: "Yesterday you identified your saboteur patterns. Today you start catching them in real time — and the tracking itself is the intervention. The gap between a trigger happening and your automatic response is usually invisible. It happens so fast that the saboteur feels like 'just who I am' rather than a pattern you can notice and redirect. This exercise builds that gap by asking you to log each activation: what triggered it, which saboteur fired, what it said, and what you did. Over time, research on habit change suggests that awareness-based interventions like self-monitoring may produce more durable behavior change than willpower alone. The heatmap format shows your most vulnerable patterns and moments at a glance — which saboteur activates most, in which situations, and at what times of day. This log becomes the raw data for Day 18 — The Saboteur's Professional Cost. The more honest you are now, the more useful that exercise will be.",
