    id: "jetstream-day-13",
    name: "The Optionality Audit",
    modality: "cognitive",
    originator: "Mindcraft / All Minds on Deck",
    primitive: "wheelChart",
    tags: ["core-jetstream"],
    dayNumber: 13,
    whyThis: "Day 13 shifts from communication to strategy. When you feel trapped — like the PIP is the only thing that matters and you have no choices — you're more likely to make fear-based decisions: agreeing to unreasonable demands, not setting boundaries, not exploring alternatives. Optionality is the antidote to that feeling. It doesn't mean planning to leave. It means knowing that you could. That knowledge changes how you sit in every meeting, how you respond to every demand, and how you make every decision. This exercise maps four domains of optionality: financial (how long can you sustain if this doesn't work out?), legal (do you know your rights?), professional (is your resume ready? have you talked to your network?), and relational (who is in your corner?). Rating each one honestly may reveal that you have more leverage than you think — or that specific areas need urgent attention. Either way, seeing the full picture tends to reduce the ambient anxiety that comes from not knowing.",
    instruction: "Drag each point on the wheel to rate your current optionality in that domain — 1 at the center (no options, no information) to 10 at the edge (fully resourced, well-informed). The four domains are: financial optionality (how long can you sustain?), legal optionality (do you know your rights?), professional optionality (resume ready? network active?), and relational optionality (who is in your corner?). After rating all four, look at the shape: where are you strongest? Where is the biggest gap?\n\nNEXT STEPS — for each domain rated below 4, answer in your journal:\n• Financial: What is your actual runway in months? What's one expense you could reduce this week?\n• Legal: Have you researched employment rights in your state? Would a 30-minute lawyer consult give you clarity?\n• Professional: Is your resume updated? Who are 3 people you could reach out to this week?\n• Relational: Who knows what you're going through? Who would you trust to give honest advice?\n\nThis isn't about leaving — it's about agency. The person who knows they have options negotiates differently.",
