    tags: ["core-jetstream"],
    dayNumber: 24,
    whyThis: "On Day 1, you rated seven areas of disruption — psychological safety, competence confidence, professional identity, financial security, trust in the system, relational stability, and future clarity. That was your baseline, taken when everything was still raw. Now, 23 days later, you rate them again. The comparison may surprise you. Some areas will have shifted significantly — perhaps your competence confidence recovered after the evidence collection, or your relational stability improved after working with the Four Horsemen. Others may be stubbornly unchanged — or may have gotten worse as the PIP timeline progresses. Both are useful information. The areas that moved show where the work landed. The areas that didn't may point to what still needs attention in the final week, or what simply needs more time. In the sandbox, the Day 1 ratings shown here are representative placeholders. In the live program, your actual Day 1 responses would be pulled in automatically.",
    instruction: "The left bars show your Day 1 ratings for each of the seven PIP disruptions. In the right column, rate each one again on the same 1-10 scale based on where you are today. The animated comparison shows the delta — where you moved the most and where you're stuck. For any area that barely moved, ask yourself in your journal: is this because it genuinely hasn't shifted, or because you haven't looked at it directly? The areas that persist may need focused attention in your final week. For each area that barely moved, write one concrete action for your final week — a conversation to have, a resource to seek, or a daily practice to start.",
