      turns: [
        { id: "t1", voice: "detective", prompt: "Recall a recent 1:1 or interaction. What did your manager pay attention to?", content: "In our first 1:1, my manager spent 20 minutes asking about my previous role and almost no time on deliverables. They asked twice who I'd met so far and whether I'd had coffee with the design lead." },
        { id: "t2", voice: "pattern", content: "Relationships matter more to them than output right now. They want to know I'm building connections, not just shipping work. The implicit expectation: prove you belong here socially before proving you can deliver." },
        { id: "t3", voice: "detective", prompt: "How do they respond to updates vs. risks? Notice the difference.", content: "When I sent a detailed status update, they replied with one line: 'Thanks, looks good.' When I mentioned a risk in our standup, they immediately asked three follow-up questions and scheduled a separate call." },
        { id: "t4", voice: "pattern", content: "They don't need details when things are fine — they need early warning when things aren't. The implicit contract: don't make them ask about problems. Surface risks proactively." },
      ],
